{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Storing a PASS review summary is blocked when any stored dimension finding for the same round has a FAIL verdict.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is module handoff: summary-write path must query/read persisted per-dimension findings for the same round before allowing PASS. Unit is too low because the bug appears when storage read + gate/write policy are wired together. Rejected System/Agentic/Workflow: behavior text is about stored verdict consistency, with no required real OS/network/subprocess or model-output dependence.","test_description":"Use real local persistence (test DB) with findings rows for one round including at least one FAIL. Attempt to persist PASS summary through the normal service/API path; assert write is rejected and error explains conflicting stored FAIL.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Adversarial critique: if production enforces this only via DB trigger/constraint, a pure in-memory repository fake could miss it; keep integration with actual local DB wiring.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.76,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Stop-gate verdict computation reads per-dimension stored findings directly and does not rely only on hand-written summary text.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The defect is wrong data source selection across modules (gate logic + repository), not a single pure function. Need to prove gate ignores misleading summary text when stored findings disagree. Rejected higher levels: no behavior text requiring real subprocess/network or AI decision quality.","test_description":"Seed storage with per-dimension findings containing FAIL and a conflicting manual summary text claiming all PASS. Invoke stop-gate computation via normal gate entrypoint; assert verdict is FAIL/escalate based on stored findings, not summary text.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Adversarial critique: if gate computes verdict in one pure function from already-loaded objects, a strong unit test could catch it; integration remains safer because bug source was persistence-vs-summary wiring.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.23,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Manual summary text overrides require an explicit override flag and produce an auditable warning record.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Two-module contract: authorization/flag check plus audit-record emission/persistence. Real failure appears when write path and audit sink interact. Unit is insufficient for missing audit persistence side effects. Rejected higher levels: no real OS/network requirement and no model-content dependence.","test_description":"Run through summary submission API/service twice: (1) manual override text without override flag -> reject; (2) with explicit override flag -> accept but assert warning audit record is persisted with actor, timestamp, and reason.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Adversarial critique: if audit is just an in-memory event bus in prod adapters, integration with only mocks could overstate coverage; include real local audit store/table in test harness.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.16,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"After Phase 4 fixes, the gate requires a review round identifier produced after the latest fix commit before PASS can be finalized.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Core failure is temporal/state linkage across commit metadata and review-round metadata. This is cross-module orchestration (fix-tracker + round-tracker + gate). Rejected System: behavior text does not require real git subprocess; commit/round IDs can be supplied as persisted metadata. Rejected Agentic/Workflow: correctness here is freshness linkage, not model judgment.","test_description":"Create state with latest fix commit C2 and only prior review round tied to C1. Attempt PASS finalization and assert block. Then create a review round record tied to C2 (or later) and assert PASS can proceed if other gates pass.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Adversarial critique: if implementation derives commit recency via `git` subprocess/OS timestamps, System could be required; disqualifier in behavior text is metadata requirement, not git command behavior.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"In the live review loop, PASS cannot finalize unless a fresh review-agent round runs on the updated diff.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires live loop sequencing: update diff -> run fresh review-agent round -> finalize gate. This is multiple staged steps with an agent run in the middle; failure appears in end-to-end orchestration, not isolated logic. Rejected Integration by INTEGRATION-BRAKE(d): handoff correctness depends on agent-stage execution in sequence. Rejected pure Agentic: this is not only one model call quality; it is pipeline sequencing across stages.","test_description":"Execute a live-like pipeline: start with prior round on old diff, apply fix producing updated diff, attempt finalization without new agent round (must block), then run a new review-agent round on updated diff and retry finalization (allowed only if findings permit). Assert freshness token/round ID is from post-fix run.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Adversarial critique: if product marks 'round ran' via deterministic job metadata and no real model call is required, Agentic may be unnecessary; Workflow still minimal because the bug is sequential stage enforcement across loop steps.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.21,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.3,"Workflow":0.42}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"If review rounds are exhausted with unresolved MUST-FIX findings in stored results, the outcome is escalation rather than PASS.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Deterministic policy over persisted state: round counter + stored MUST-FIX findings -> escalation. Real failure is repository/state-machine interaction. No required real OS/network, and no dependence on model output quality for this rule.","test_description":"Seed stored results with unresolved MUST-FIX findings and set round budget exhausted. Invoke decision engine through service boundary; assert outcome is escalation and PASS is blocked.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Adversarial critique: could be Unit if decision function directly receives plain structs; integration chosen because exhaustion and unresolved findings commonly come from separate modules/stores and that handoff caused similar regressions.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.28,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"In a live multi-round review workflow, exhausted rounds with unresolved MUST-FIX findings still block PASS and emit escalation.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Behavior is explicitly live and multi-round, requiring sequential round progression plus terminal escalation emission. Failure boundary is full pipeline behavior over multiple rounds, not one function. Rejected Integration: INTEGRATION-BRAKE(c,d) applies because correctness depends on cross-stage handoff across rounds in a live workflow.","test_description":"Run an end-to-end multi-round loop with configured max rounds. Ensure unresolved MUST-FIX persists across rounds, exhaust allowed rounds, then assert final state blocks PASS and emits escalation event/record exactly once.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Adversarial critique: if rounds are simulated as static records without executing loop transitions, integration may appear enough; keep workflow to catch real sequencing/termination regressions.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.16,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.18,"Workflow":0.6}}]}
